	<div class="blog-archive-entries-wrapper">
		<div id="unique-entry-id-332" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">New Game</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 29 May 2010 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-pirates.php">Pirates</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="mouse" src="mouse.jpg" width="41" height="41" /></div>I am still not really allowed to say anything but at PrairieCon my husband and two friends are launching a card game that includs pirates.  The online version should follow about a month later.<br /><br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-334" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">New Blog Entry</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Wednesday, 26 May 2010 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>Justin has published a new blog entry.<br />Sorry just spotted it, this is when the message should have been written.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-329" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Not much happening</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 22 May 2010 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-side-tracked.php">Side Tracked</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="mouse" src="mouse.jpg" width="41" height="41" /></div>I do have something to write on the blog for next week but at the moment it is all quiet, which probably means I am missing something.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-330" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Links</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Sunday, 16 May 2010 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-tempesttwins.php">TempestTwins</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="mouse" src="mouse.jpg" width="41" height="41" /></div>A little while back I mentioned a study about links on the internet.  The one person who replied agreed with the study and I am slowly working through the website changing the links.  Thank you for your patience.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-328" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Pirate Party UK</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Friday, 07 May 2010 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-pirates.php">Pirates</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="priate party uk" src="pirateparty.png" width="102" height="46" /></div>The Pirate Party UK's Blog entry post election (I found it interesting and so here is part of it. Dated 7th May 2010 by John Barron)<br /><br />"After a lot of hard work on all sides, we've just fought our first election as the UK pirate party.  Across 9 seats, by my calculations we polled 0.34%, for a total of 1340 votes. Our best result was in Manchester Gorton, where our candidate Tim Dobson polled 236 votes for 0.62% of the vote.  Before this election, we didn't know what level of support we could expect. Nor did we know how to organise ourselves, or how to navigate the election requirements and comply with the law. So this has been a tremendous learning experience for everyone involved ..."<br /><br />For the whole blog entry please see <a href="http://www.pirateparty.org.uk/blog/2010/may/7/everything-starts-somewhere/" rel="self" title="www.pirateparty.org.uk">www.pirateparty.org.uk/blog/2010/may/7/everything-starts-somewhere</a><br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-327" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Cities of London and Westminster</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Friday, 07 May 2010 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-pirates.php">Pirates</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="ship" src="ship.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>If you wondering what happened in the Cities of London and Westminster ward - Conservatives got in, but looking at the election results any area with people with money were voting in the blues.<br /><br />For the two different pirate candidates, I thought you might like to hear how they did.<br />Jack Nunn of the Pirate Party UK got 90 votes (0.2 of the number of votes cast)<br />Mad Cap'n Tom the Independent candidate got 84 (0.2 of the number of votes cast)<br />So both candidates lost their deposits.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-326" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Whoops</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Sunday, 02 May 2010 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-tempesttwins.php">TempestTwins</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="mouse" src="mouse.jpg" width="41" height="41" /></div>Sorry I forgot to publish the last blog entry.<br />The competition ends in a weeks time (sorry this post last you the second week).  Anyway the competitions usually go out around the last Friday of each month.<br /></div></div>
	</div>
	
	 
